parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS HCU can cause the loss of front or rear brakes, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front brake lever is frozen and cannot be depressed
the front brakes do not work
the brakes lock up while driving
the loss of braking system functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Rear Wheel Assembly (Smooth Spoke Wheels)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective rear wheel assembly can cause sudden tire deflation, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected rear tire deflation
especially when cornering or braking
causing the motorcycle to slide or wash out
and potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end steering wobble can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds. This issue can be particularly dangerous when decelerating or taking hands off the handlebars.
symptoms: The front end of the motorcycle wobbles or shakes
especially during deceleration or when taking hands off the handlebars
making it difficult to maintain straight and level riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine heat can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Prolonged exposure to high temperatures can also cause burns to the rider and passenger, and potentially lead to clothing catching fire.
symptoms: The engine overheats
especially when idling or at low speeds
the motorcycle stalls when the throttle is applied
high cylinder temperatures (measured at 280°F in the front cylinder and 380°F in the rear cylinder)
unbearable heat emanating from the engine
discomfort and heat stress for the rider and passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ineffective Engine Idle Temperature Management System (EITMS)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EITMS to regulate engine temperature can lead to excessive engine heat, causing discomfort, heat stress, and potentially even burns to the rider and passenger.
symptoms: The engine overheats
especially when idling or at low speeds
the EITMS fails to reduce engine temperature
high cylinder temperatures
unbearable heat emanating from the engine.
